 {"id":"frankenredis-iz1j","title":"Implement replication backlog buffer that stores command bytes for partial resync","description":"# Replication Backlog Buffer\n\n## What\nThe existing `BacklogWindow` in fr-repl tracks replication offsets (replid, start offset, size) but does NOT store actual command bytes. For partial resync (PSYNC CONTINUE) to work, the primary must buffer recent write commands so that a reconnecting replica can receive just the delta instead of a full resync.\n\n## Current State\n- `BacklogWindow` struct exists with replid, start_offset, size fields\n- `decide_psync()` checks if requested offset falls within the backlog window\n- But no actual byte buffer exists — when CONTINUE is decided, there are no bytes to send\n\n## Implementation\n1. Add a `backlog_bytes: VecDeque<u8>` field to the replication state (either in ServerState or a new BacklogBuffer struct)\n2. Configure max size via `repl-backlog-size` (already a config knob, default 1 MiB)\n3. After each write command is propagated, append its RESP-serialized bytes to the backlog\n4. When backlog exceeds max size, drain from the front (oldest bytes)\n5. Track the byte offset corresponding to the front of the buffer\n6. On PSYNC CONTINUE: calculate the byte range the replica needs, send those bytes\n7. On PSYNC FULLRESYNC: reset backlog after snapshot send\n\n## Unit Tests\n- Test 1: Append 100 commands, verify backlog size stays within limit\n- Test 2: Partial resync — append commands, request offset in range, verify correct bytes returned\n- Test 3: Offset out of range — verify FULLRESYNC fallback\n- Test 4: Backlog wraps — oldest bytes evicted when limit reached\n- Test 5: Reset on FULLRESYNC — verify backlog clears\n\n## Depends On\n- REPLICAOF TCP client (1v8b) — need connection before backlog matters\n- Must be done BEFORE command propagation (1ng7) — propagation writes to this buffer\n\n## Files\n- crates/fr-repl/src/lib.rs (backlog buffer struct + methods)\n- crates/fr-runtime/src/lib.rs (wire backlog into server state)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-07T04:15:36.338674922Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-07T18:54:13.005179144Z","closed_at":"2026-04-07T18:54:13.004893794Z","close_reason":"Already implemented: aof_records Vec<AofRecord> in ServerState stores command bytes, encoded_aof_stream_from_offset() extracts delta for partial resync, PSYNC CONTINUE handler at main.rs:1642-1644 sends backlog bytes to reconnecting replicas.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"frankenredis-iz1j","depends_on_id":"frankenredis-1v8b","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-04-07T04:16:13.676226414Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
